# =============================================================================
# Ham dashboard — copy to `.env.local` (or set in your host’s env UI).
# Model / OpenRouter keys live on the FastAPI backend (repo root `.env`), not here.
# =============================================================================

# --- Ham API (chat, context, workspace APIs) ---
#
# Local development
#   Leave VITE_HAM_API_BASE unset. The app calls same-origin `/api/*`; Vite proxies
#   to FastAPI (see `vite.config.ts`).
#
# Production (Vercel, static host, etc.)
#   Set VITE_HAM_API_BASE to your deployed Ham API origin — no path, no trailing slash,
#   and no /api suffix (the app appends /api/... itself).
#   Set it for Production and Preview, then redeploy (Vite embeds VITE_* at build time).
#
# VITE_HAM_API_BASE=https://your-ham-api-xxxxx.run.app
# Wrong: https://your-ham-api.run.app/api

# Optional — dev / `vite preview` only: where `/api` is proxied (default http://127.0.0.1:8000).
# VITE_HAM_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8000

# =============================================================================
# Optional — not used by the current Ham UI (no imports in `src/`).
# Kept because `vite.config.ts` still injects `process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY` for
# `@google/genai` if you add browser-side Gemini later.
# =============================================================================

# Google AI Studio / Gemini API key (only if you wire client-side calls yourself).
# GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Public site URL — not referenced by this frontend today; useful if you add OAuth
# or absolute callback URLs later.
# APP_URL=https://your-dashboard.example.com
